 By Obi Nwakanma I am presently in South Africa, in resident as a fellow at the Stellenbosch Institute of Advanced Studies (STIAS), in Stellenbosch, the Western Cape. Early in the week I began to receive numerous calls and messages, and texts, and all manners of verbal and non-verbal signals in inquiring about my health and safety in South Africa from friends and members of my family. I assured them that I was safe and sound under the warm and friendly care of the folks at STIAS who have so far shown me and the many fellows in residence nothing but kindness and generosity. Continue reading Tit for South Africa, tat for Nigeria at Vanguard News. Source: Vanguard